definition: to take possession of/to occupy/to take up

sentences.english: A large press, inlaid with agate and lapis-lazuli, filled one.
sentences.chinese: 一个镶嵌着玛瑙和琉璃的大衣柜占满了墙的一角。

sentences.english: I am afraid all the tables by the window are taken.
sentences.chinese: 恐怕窗边的桌子都占满了。

sentences.english: When a group of women got on the car, every seat was already occupied.
sentences.chinese: 当一群妇女上车之后，车上的座位全都被占满了。

sentences.english: A small anteroom was almost completely dominated by a Ping-Pong table.
sentences.chinese: 一个小小的前厅几乎被一张乒乓球桌占满。

sentences.english: Don't trade your life for temporary things.
sentences.chinese: 故此，不要让短暂的事占满你的生命。

sentences.english: Advertisements often fill in two pages of the evening paper.
sentences.chinese: 广告常占满这家晚报的两页。

sentences.english: Sometimes a row goes all the way around a wall.
sentences.chinese: 有时一行会占满整堵墙。

sentences.english: You don't have to always fill the entire grid unit either.
sentences.chinese: 你也不必总是占满整个单元格。

sentences.english: Since then, my world is full filled your emotion.
sentences.chinese: 从此，我的情感世界被你全占满。

sentences.english: Even worse, after a few minutes pass, I notice that our uplinks again start to become saturated.
sentences.chinese: 更遭的是，几分钟后，我发现上行链路又被占满了。

sentences.english: Her time is fully taken uD with writing.
sentences.chinese: 她的时间完全被写作占满了。

sentences.english: His luggage filled the entire taxi.
sentences.chinese: 他的行李把出租车的车箱都占满了。

sentences.english: The entire first floor will be filled with 200 containers like this one.
sentences.chinese: 整个一楼将被两百个这样的集装箱占满。

crowded to bursting point/filled to overflowing/jam-packed
congestion/to block/to congest/to crowd/to choke/to cram/to fill up/to stuff/to take up all the space
to seize/to push aside and occupy
to submerge/to drown/to flood/to drown out (also fig.)
to be full of/to flood/to congest
numerous and close together/densely packed/thickly dotted/thick/dense
